body:
Fixes #3089 for me too.

@MicroJOo: Regarding the 'dumb' thing where a harv on the pad gets pushed away - this happens seemingly only very rarely. If I had to guess I imagine the 2nd harv has priority for the pad but when it's bumping the 1st one away it actually bumps it towards the pad by chance.

Anyway it happened so rarely and the delay was so minor I'm not worried about it myself.

@Rydra: You still need to amend your commit message so it is correct. :+1: after that.
